# decision-golden.json.meta — provenance sidecar for decision-golden.json (issue #396, R5).
#
# Captured by running the PRE-CHANGE (byte-identical-passthrough) code —
# `check_deps_resolved` (lib-dispatch.sh), `mark-issue-checkbox.sh`, the
# `autonomous-review.sh` no-auto-close gate logic, the `status.sh` state/labels
# read, and the `autonomous-dev.sh` issue-body fetch — against a stubbed `gh`
# serving each scenario below, on the FIRST TDD commit of the #396 W1b branch
# (before the abstract-contract rewrite landed). Sourced files: the pre-#396
# `git show main:...` snapshots of lib-dispatch.sh, lib-issue-provider.sh,
# providers/itp-github.sh, and mark-issue-checkbox.sh.
#
# Scenarios captured:
#   check_deps_resolved:
#     normal_closed — body has `## Dependencies\n- #42\n`, dep #42 state CLOSED
#       → rc 0 (resolved).
#     open_blocks — same body, dep #42 state OPEN → rc 1 (blocked).
#     no_deps_section — body has no `## Dependencies` heading → rc 0 (no-op).
#   mark_checkbox (real `mark-issue-checkbox.sh` subprocess, symlink-sandboxed
#     per the test-itp-write-leaves.sh convention so `readlink -f` resolves the
#     provider seam):
#     happy_rewrite — body has `- [ ] Do the thing` unchecked → rc 0, stdout
#       "Checked: Do the thing", PATCH body carries `- [x] Do the thing`.
#     already_checked — body has `- [x] Do the thing` already → rc 0, stdout
#       "Already checked: Do the thing", no PATCH call.
#   no_auto_close (autonomous-review.sh's `HAS_NO_AUTO_CLOSE` derivation):
#     present — labels include `no-auto-close` → "true".
#     absent — labels exclude `no-auto-close` → "false".
#   status_next_action (status.sh's ISSUE_STATE/LABELS read + `_next_action`-
#     relevant branch, reproduced inline since `_next_action` itself is a
#     status.sh-internal function):
#     open — state OPEN, labels `pending-dev` → "OPEN:LABELS=pending-dev"
#       (not terminal branch).
#     closed — state CLOSED, labels `approved` → "TERMINAL:CLOSED:LABELS=approved"
#       (terminal branch).
#   dev_fetch (autonomous-dev.sh's ISSUE_BODY capture — the raw gh payload
#     forwarded through `-q '.'`, textual title/body parity only per R5; the
#     labels/comments SHAPE change is documented, not parity-pinned):
#     title_body_comments — the primary fetch (`title,body,comments -q '.'`).
#     resume_title_body — the resume-fallback fetch (`title,body -q '.'`).
#
# Regenerate (only if the OLD pre-#396 semantics are ever in dispute): checkout
# the commit immediately before #396's leaf rewrite (`main` at the time this
# file was authored), extract lib-dispatch.sh / lib-issue-provider.sh /
# providers/itp-github.sh / mark-issue-checkbox.sh via `git show`, and re-run
# each scenario's stub-gh harness described above.
